Fix root cause: bundle all server dependencies into server.cjs

The real reason the server never started was that server.cjs was only
50 KB — all npm packages (express, cors, drizzle-orm, etc.) were marked
external and not bundled. When the utility process ran server.cjs from
resources/ in the packaged app, require('express') immediately failed
because node_modules is not accessible from that location. The server
always crashed before ever listening on port 5001.

Fix:
  script/build.electron.ts
  - Removed getAllPackageNames() helper — no longer needed
  - Changed server esbuild external list from [...allPkgs] to only:
      ["electron", "bufferutil", "utf-8-validate", "pg-native"]
    All other npm packages (express, cors, drizzle-orm, pg, multer,
    etc.) are now bundled directly into server.cjs
  - Added alias: { "@shared": path.resolve("shared") } so esbuild
    correctly resolves the @shared/* TypeScript path alias
  - With platform:"node", all Node.js built-ins (including node:sqlite)
    are automatically external — no explicit listing needed

Result:
  server.cjs will be self-contained (~10–20 MB instead of 50 KB).
  The utility process can now load it cleanly from resources/ with no
  external dependencies required at runtime.
